description:
## Task 3: Frontend type extension

Extend the `UserDeletionImpact` TypeScript interface with the three new fields the backend now returns.

### Files
- **Modify:** [ui/frontend/src/types/admin.ts](../../../ui/frontend/src/types/admin.ts) (lines 19–27)

### Canonical reference
[Plan § Task 3](../plans/2026-05-13-admin-user-management.md) — has the exact TypeScript shape.

### Change
Insert `total_export_jobs`, `total_sync_jobs`, `total_sync_configs` between `total_import_jobs` and `total_sessions` so the field order matches the backend JSON response.

Final shape:
```typescript
export interface UserDeletionImpact {
  user_id: string;
  username: string;
  total_games: number;
  total_tags: number;
  total_import_jobs: number;
  total_export_jobs: number;
  total_sync_jobs: number;
  total_sync_configs: number;
  total_sessions: number;
  warning: string;
}
```

### Expected fallout
After this change, `npm run check` (from `ui/frontend/`) will flag the MSW mock in `admin.test.ts` and the deletion-impact table in `$id.tsx` as missing fields. **This is expected** — Tasks 4 and 5 close those gaps.

### Quality gate
The check is best run after Task 3 is committed alone. Don't try to clear all TS errors in this task — the type extension itself must land first so the dependent tasks have a stable interface to target.
